ğŸ§© How It Works

The script chains together multiple Linux text-processing tools:

Tool	Purpose
grep	Find patterns, warnings, failures
sed	Clean or normalize text lines
awk	Extract structured data
cut	Extract fixed-position fields
find	Scan directories for files
sort + uniq	Summaries & deduplication
wc	Counting events

These are combined using pipelines (|) to produce fast, accurate analysis output.

ğŸ”’ Security Best Practices Included

Never alters user filesâ€”only reads.

Detects misconfigured permissions (777).

Highlights possible security breaches.

Encourages proper triage instead of modifying or deleting user data.

